005package edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command;
006
007import static edu.wpi.first.units.Units.MetersPerSecond;
008import static edu.wpi.first.units.Units.Volts;
009import static edu.wpi.first.util.ErrorMessages.requireNonNullParam;
010
011import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.PIDController;
012import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.RamseteController;
013import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.SimpleMotorFeedforward;
014import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d;
015import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds;
016import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.DifferentialDriveKinematics;
017import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds;
018import edu.wpi.first.math.trajectory.Trajectory;
019import edu.wpi.first.units.Distance;
020import edu.wpi.first.units.MutableMeasure;
021import edu.wpi.first.units.Velocity;
022import edu.wpi.first.util.sendable.SendableBuilder;
023import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Timer;
024import java.util.function.BiConsumer;
025import java.util.function.Supplier;
026
027/**
028 * A command that uses a RAMSETE controller ({@link RamseteController}) to follow a trajectory
029 * {@link Trajectory} with a differential drive.
030 *
031 * <p>The command handles trajectory-following, PID calculations, and feedforwards internally. This
032 * is intended to be a more-or-less "complete solution" that can be used by teams without a great
033 * deal of controls expertise.
034 *
035 * <p>Advanced teams seeking more flexibility (for example, those who wish to use the onboard PID
036 * functionality of a "smart" motor controller) may use the secondary constructor that omits the PID
037 * and feedforward functionality, returning only the raw wheel speeds from the RAMSETE controller.
038 *
039 * <p>This class is provided by the NewCommands VendorDep
040 */
041public class RamseteCommand extends Command {
042  private final Timer m_timer = new Timer();
043  private final boolean m_usePID;
044  private final Trajectory m_trajectory;
045  private final Supplier<Pose2d> m_pose;
046  private final RamseteController m_follower;
047  private final SimpleMotorFeedforward m_feedforward;
048  private final DifferentialDriveKinematics m_kinematics;
049  private final Supplier<DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds> m_speeds;
050  private final PIDController m_leftController;
051  private final PIDController m_rightController;
052  private final BiConsumer<Double, Double> m_output;
053  private DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds m_prevSpeeds = new DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds();
054  private final MutableMeasure<Velocity<Distance>> m_prevLeftSpeedSetpoint =
055      MutableMeasure.zero(MetersPerSecond);
056  private final MutableMeasure<Velocity<Distance>> m_prevRightSpeedSetpoint =
057      MutableMeasure.zero(MetersPerSecond);
058  private final MutableMeasure<Velocity<Distance>> m_leftSpeedSetpoint =
059      MutableMeasure.zero(MetersPerSecond);
060  private final MutableMeasure<Velocity<Distance>> m_rightSpeedSetpoint =
061      MutableMeasure.zero(MetersPerSecond);
062  private double m_prevTime;
063
064  /**
065   * Constructs a new RamseteCommand that, when executed, will follow the provided trajectory. PID
066   * control and feedforward are handled internally, and outputs are scaled -12 to 12 representing
067   * units of volts.
068   *
069   * <p>Note: The controller will *not* set the outputVolts to zero upon completion of the path -
070   * this is left to the user, since it is not appropriate for paths with nonstationary endstates.
071   *
072   * @param trajectory The trajectory to follow.
073   * @param pose A function that supplies the robot pose - use one of the odometry classes to
074   *     provide this.
075   * @param controller The RAMSETE controller used to follow the trajectory.
076   * @param feedforward The feedforward to use for the drive.
077   * @param kinematics The kinematics for the robot drivetrain.
078   * @param wheelSpeeds A function that supplies the speeds of the left and right sides of the robot
079   *     drive.
080   * @param leftController The PIDController for the left side of the robot drive.
081   * @param rightController The PIDController for the right side of the robot drive.
082   * @param outputVolts A function that consumes the computed left and right outputs (in volts) for
083   *     the robot drive.
084   * @param requirements The subsystems to require.
085   * @deprecated Use LTVUnicycleController instead.
086   */
087  @Deprecated(since = "2025", forRemoval = true)
088  @SuppressWarnings("this-escape")
089  public RamseteCommand(
090      Trajectory trajectory,
091      Supplier<Pose2d> pose,
092      RamseteController controller,
093      SimpleMotorFeedforward feedforward,
094      DifferentialDriveKinematics kinematics,
095      Supplier<DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds> wheelSpeeds,
096      PIDController leftController,
097      PIDController rightController,
098      BiConsumer<Double, Double> outputVolts,
099      Subsystem... requirements) {
100    m_trajectory = requireNonNullParam(trajectory, "trajectory", "RamseteCommand");
101    m_pose = requireNonNullParam(pose, "pose", "RamseteCommand");
102    m_follower = requireNonNullParam(controller, "controller", "RamseteCommand");
103    m_feedforward = feedforward;
104    m_kinematics = requireNonNullParam(kinematics, "kinematics", "RamseteCommand");
105    m_speeds = requireNonNullParam(wheelSpeeds, "wheelSpeeds", "RamseteCommand");
106    m_leftController = requireNonNullParam(leftController, "leftController", "RamseteCommand");
107    m_rightController = requireNonNullParam(rightController, "rightController", "RamseteCommand");
108    m_output = requireNonNullParam(outputVolts, "outputVolts", "RamseteCommand");
109
110    m_usePID = true;
111
112    addRequirements(requirements);
113  }
114
115  /**
116   * Constructs a new RamseteCommand that, when executed, will follow the provided trajectory.
117   * Performs no PID control and calculates no feedforwards; outputs are the raw wheel speeds from
118   * the RAMSETE controller, and will need to be converted into a usable form by the user.
119   *
120   * @param trajectory The trajectory to follow.
121   * @param pose A function that supplies the robot pose - use one of the odometry classes to
122   *     provide this.
123   * @param follower The RAMSETE follower used to follow the trajectory.
124   * @param kinematics The kinematics for the robot drivetrain.
125   * @param outputMetersPerSecond A function that consumes the computed left and right wheel speeds.
126   * @param requirements The subsystems to require.
127   * @deprecated Use LTVUnicycleController instead.
128   */
129  @Deprecated(since = "2025", forRemoval = true)
130  @SuppressWarnings("this-escape")
131  public RamseteCommand(
132      Trajectory trajectory,
133      Supplier<Pose2d> pose,
134      RamseteController follower,
135      DifferentialDriveKinematics kinematics,
136      BiConsumer<Double, Double> outputMetersPerSecond,
137      Subsystem... requirements) {
138    m_trajectory = requireNonNullParam(trajectory, "trajectory", "RamseteCommand");
139    m_pose = requireNonNullParam(pose, "pose", "RamseteCommand");
140    m_follower = requireNonNullParam(follower, "follower", "RamseteCommand");
141    m_kinematics = requireNonNullParam(kinematics, "kinematics", "RamseteCommand");
142    m_output =
143        requireNonNullParam(outputMetersPerSecond, "outputMetersPerSecond", "RamseteCommand");
144
145    m_feedforward = null;
146    m_speeds = null;
147    m_leftController = null;
148    m_rightController = null;
149
150    m_usePID = false;
151
152    addRequirements(requirements);
153  }
154
155  @Override
156  public void initialize() {
157    m_prevTime = -1;
158    var initialState = m_trajectory.sample(0);
159    m_prevSpeeds =
160        m_kinematics.toWheelSpeeds(
161            new ChassisSpeeds(
162                initialState.velocityMetersPerSecond,
163                0,
164                initialState.curvatureRadPerMeter * initialState.velocityMetersPerSecond));
165    m_prevLeftSpeedSetpoint.mut_setMagnitude(m_prevSpeeds.leftMetersPerSecond);
166    m_prevRightSpeedSetpoint.mut_setMagnitude(m_prevSpeeds.rightMetersPerSecond);
167    m_timer.restart();
168    if (m_usePID) {
169      m_leftController.reset();
170      m_rightController.reset();
171    }
172  }
173
174  @Override
175  public void execute() {
176    double curTime = m_timer.get();
177
178    if (m_prevTime < 0) {
179      m_output.accept(0.0, 0.0);
180      m_prevTime = curTime;
181      return;
182    }
183
184    var targetWheelSpeeds =
185        m_kinematics.toWheelSpeeds(
186            m_follower.calculate(m_pose.get(), m_trajectory.sample(curTime)));
187
188    var leftSpeedSetpoint = targetWheelSpeeds.leftMetersPerSecond;
189    var rightSpeedSetpoint = targetWheelSpeeds.rightMetersPerSecond;
190
191    m_leftSpeedSetpoint.mut_setMagnitude(targetWheelSpeeds.leftMetersPerSecond);
192    m_rightSpeedSetpoint.mut_setMagnitude(targetWheelSpeeds.rightMetersPerSecond);
193
194    double leftOutput;
195    double rightOutput;
196
197    if (m_usePID) {
198      double leftFeedforward =
199          m_feedforward.calculate(m_prevLeftSpeedSetpoint, m_leftSpeedSetpoint).in(Volts);
200
201      double rightFeedforward =
202          m_feedforward.calculate(m_prevRightSpeedSetpoint, m_rightSpeedSetpoint).in(Volts);
203
204      leftOutput =
205          leftFeedforward
206              + m_leftController.calculate(m_speeds.get().leftMetersPerSecond, leftSpeedSetpoint);
207
208      rightOutput =
209          rightFeedforward
210              + m_rightController.calculate(
211                  m_speeds.get().rightMetersPerSecond, rightSpeedSetpoint);
212    } else {
213      leftOutput = leftSpeedSetpoint;
214      rightOutput = rightSpeedSetpoint;
215    }
216
217    m_output.accept(leftOutput, rightOutput);
218    m_prevSpeeds = targetWheelSpeeds;
219    m_prevTime = curTime;
220  }
221
222  @Override
223  public void end(boolean interrupted) {
224    m_timer.stop();
225
226    if (interrupted) {
227      m_output.accept(0.0, 0.0);
228    }
229  }
230
231  @Override
232  public boolean isFinished() {
233    return m_timer.hasElapsed(m_trajectory.getTotalTimeSeconds());
234  }
235
236  @Override
237  public void initSendable(SendableBuilder builder) {
238    super.initSendable(builder);
239    builder.addDoubleProperty("leftVelocity", () -> m_prevSpeeds.leftMetersPerSecond, null);
240    builder.addDoubleProperty("rightVelocity", () -> m_prevSpeeds.rightMetersPerSecond, null);
241  }
242}
